observations.recommendation:
We recommended the Municipal Mayor to:

require the Municipal Health Officer to look into ways on how to fully-address the proper implementation of the program for the immediate benefit of intended beneficiaries; 



instruct the Bids and Awards Committee to seek for bonafide suppliers of medicines with good track record to join the bidding process.

We recommended the Municipal Mayor to:

instruct the Municipal Accountant to reverse the unsupported adjusting entry for fair presentation of the financial statements;

require the Municipal Treasurer to deposit the amount of P1,291,435.49 to the account of the National Treasury in order to provide the national government of additional funds for other vital projects/programs, in relation to Observation No. 4 of CY 2015 Annual Audit Report.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the Municipal Assessor to:

make follow-ups on the status of the approval of the application for Special Patent/Sketch Plan of the two lots embodied in CY 2014 AAR to facilitate the titling of the lots in the name of the Municipality;



take the necessary steps/action in the titling of the other three lots in the name of the Municipality to avoid third party claims that may arise in the future.

We recommended the Municipal Mayor to:

instruct the Bids and Awards Committee to submit a written explanation on why the projects were awarded despite the non-submission of a valid/updated tax clearance, at the time of bidding, and why the said transactions should not be disallowed in audit;

require the Bids and Awards Committee to verify all documents submitted by bidders and ensure that they are eligible, prior to award of the projects/contracts.
